title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 – Oct 28 2022
itunes:title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 – Oct 28 2022
description:
The blue bird is freed! Musk takes over Twitter, fires top executives, libs freak out. Clay says, "The people who say they're going to leave Twitter are the people who said they were going to Canada when Trump got elected -- and didn't." Polls look good for GOP. McConnell funding RINO Lisa Murkowski in Alaska over conservative Kelly Tshibaka is outrageous. Desperate Biden straight-up lies about gas prices and inflation. C&B wonder if those lies were planted in the teleprompter because his staff knows he will read anything on the teleprompter. Fetterman's wife says, "Swimming in America is very racist." Buck addresses Trump and Twitter: "I don't think Trump will be able to pull off with the same panache what he did in 2016 without going back on Twitter."

Follow Clay & Buck on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/c/clayandbuck
